        <h3>1. Bed Leveling</h3>
        <p>Use the built-in sensors or manual adjustment to ensure proper bed leveling. Follow these steps:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Heat the bed to 60°C</li>
            <li>Perform auto-leveling if available</li>
            <li>Check with a piece of paper for consistent resistance</li>
        </ol>
        <h3>2. Extruder Calibration</h3>
        <p>Measure and adjust the extrusion rate:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Measure 100mm of filament</li>
            <li>Extrude 100mm at 100% speed</li>
            <li>Measure actual length and calculate correction factor</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>3. Temperature Calibration</h3>
        <p>Verify nozzle and bed temperatures with a calibrated thermometer.</p>
